# Windows Herd + Git Bash (pgi-core-frontend)

## PHP is never bare `php` in Git Bash (unless PATH set)

| Do | Don't |
|----|--------|
| `export PATH="/c/Users/PGI/.config/herd/bin:$PATH"` | Assume `php` works |
| `/c/Users/PGI/.config/herd/bin/php.bat artisan …` | Install separate PHP |

## Project paths

| Item | Path |
|------|------|
| Repo | `/d/vitou/projects/pgi-core-frontend` |
| PHP (Herd) | **8.2.x** — matches `composer.json` `"php": "^8.2"` |
| Herd site | `APP_URL` in `.env` (e.g. `http://pgi-core-frontend.test`) |
| Vite dev | `npm run dev` (HMR; browse via `APP_URL`, not :5173 alone) |
| Build | `npm run build` |

## Common commands

```bash
export PATH="/c/Users/PGI/.config/herd/bin:$PATH"
cd /d/vitou/projects/pgi-core-frontend

php artisan test
npm run build
node scripts/verify-burglary-routing.mjs
```

## Known failures (fix, don't re-investigate)

| Error | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| `php` not found | `export PATH="/c/Users/PGI/.config/herd/bin:$PATH"` |
| `vendor/autoload.php` missing | `composer install` |
| Vite / assets stale | `npm run build` or `npm run dev` |
| Herd 500 / site not found | `herd link` in project dir; check `APP_URL` |

## Agent checklist

1. Run commands with PATH export or `php.bat`; show output.
2. Tell user exact `APP_URL` for browser smoke — not localhost:5173 unless Vite-only debug.
3. Verify before claiming done (`verification-before-completion`).
4. Respect PL seven-product scope (`02-pl-seven-product-scope.mdc`).
